{"word":"παράφημι","slug":"παράφημι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παράφημι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> <el>παραί-φημι</el>) (<a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> <el>πάρ-φημι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to speak gently to, to advise</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to persuade, appease</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to speak deceitfully</i> or <i>insincerely</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>; and, in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}